<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,1454,2021]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
The protologue of 
<taxonomicName box="[347,626,1455,1480]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cataractarum">
<emphasis box="[347,626,1455,1480]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Hieracium cataractarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Arvet-Touvet &amp; Huter in 
<bibRefCitation author="Arvet-Touvet, C. &amp; Gautier, G." box="[929,1323,1454,1480]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" pagination="328 - 371" refId="ref6442" refString="Arvet-Touvet, C. &amp; Gautier, G. (1894) Hieracium nouveaux pour la France ou pour l'Espagne. Bulletin de la Societe Botanique de France 41: 328 - 371. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00378941.1894.10831608" type="journal article" year="1894">Arvet-Touvet &amp; Gautier 1894: 330</bibRefCitation>
) includes a complete description in French followed by the locality “ 
<emphasis box="[774,822,1490,1516]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Hab</emphasis>
. Regnum murcicum, in rupium fissuris cataractarum los Chorros, sol. calc. 
<quantity box="[345,484,1526,1552]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" unit="m" value="900.0" valueMax="1000.0" valueMin="800.0">800–1000m</quantity>
”, and a reference to a concrete gathering “ 
<taxonomicName authority="G. Rigo" authorityName="G. Rigo" box="[954,1016,1526,1552]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyparochromidae" genus="Porta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Porta</taxonomicName>
et Rigo ex 
<emphasis box="[1144,1333,1526,1552]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Itinere hispanico</emphasis>
, III, 1891, nº 395”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,1454,2021]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
<bibRefCitation author="Gottschlich, G." box="[189,455,1598,1624]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" pagination="5 - 416" refId="ref7467" refString="Gottschlich, G. (2007) Die Gattung Hieracium L. (Compositae) im Herbarium Rupert Huter (Vinzentinum Brixen, BRIX). Kommentiertes Verzeichnis mit taxonomischen und nomenklatorischen Erganzungen unter besonderer Berucksichtigung der Typus-Belege. Veroffentlichungen des Tiroler Landesmuseums Ferdinandeum 86 (Sonderband): 5 - 416." type="book chapter" year="2007">Gottschlich (2007: 34)</bibRefCitation>
designated as the 
<typeStatus box="[683,786,1598,1624]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[835,1027,1599,1624]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cataractarum">
<emphasis box="[835,1027,1599,1624]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">H. cataractarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a specimen preserved in the Huter herbarium at 
<collectionCode box="[286,353,1635,1661]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">BRIX</collectionCode>
(no. 
<collectionCode box="[412,482,1634,1661]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">BRIX</collectionCode>
–8361), belonging to the exsiccata cited in the protologue. We have found additionally 
<specimenCount box="[136,307,1670,1696]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" type="generic">four specimens</specimenCount>
belonging to the gathering cited in the protologue (
<emphasis box="[887,1077,1670,1696]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Itinere hispanico</emphasis>
, III, 1891, nº 395) that according to Art. 9.6 and Art. 40 Note 1 of the 
<emphasis box="[558,605,1707,1733]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
<collectionCode box="[558,605,1707,1733]" country="Colombia" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/xsgz-nxkh" name="Instituto de Ciencias Naturales, Museo de Historia Natural" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">ICN</collectionCode>
</emphasis>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[666,889,1706,1733]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" refId="ref9273" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (Eds.) (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Glashutten: Koeltz Botanical Books. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="book" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis box="[763,813,1706,1732]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
), are 
<typeStatus box="[952,1054,1707,1733]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">syntypes</typeStatus>
. They are located in the herbarium 
<collectionCode box="[136,180,1742,1768]" country="Spain" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15682" name="Real Jardín Botánico" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" type="Herbarium">MA</collectionCode>
(consisting of two complete plants), 
<collectionCode box="[608,652,1743,1769]" country="United Kingdom" name="Bristol Museum" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">BM</collectionCode>
(a specimen that bears three plants, see 
<figureCitation box="[1118,1188,1742,1768]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[136,229,1536,1558]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,190,1512]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[151,1436,187,1512]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Isolectotype of Hieracium cataractarum Arv.-Touv. &amp; Huter in BM (barcode BM001050678).—Image by courtesy of The Natural History Museum, London (Herbarium BM), reproduced with permission." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5413231" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5413231/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
), 
